description: BusyBox v1.14.1 (compiled on 2017-05-19) - A multi-functional Unix toolset. No directly related CVE vulnerabilities were found, but upgrading to the latest version is recommended to obtain security fixes.

OpenSSL 1.0.2h (compiled on 2016-05-03) - Cryptographic library. Contains multiple critical vulnerabilities including CVE-2016-2177 (CVSS 9.8), CVE-2016-2176 (CVSS 8.2), etc., which may lead to remote code execution, information disclosure, and denial of service attacks.
SQLite 3.7.4 - Embedded database engine. No directly related CVE vulnerabilities found, but this version is outdated (released in 2010), recommend upgrading to the latest version.

REDACTED_SECRET_KEY_PLACEHOLDER - Multicast DNS service implementation. Version information not directly obtained; further analysis is recommended to confirm the version and identify potential vulnerabilities.
